item.title: Ha lol
item.dc:creator: @The_Un-Named The Un-Named
item.description:
@The_Un-Named wrote:

Frell, you really should learn not to poke your head in places you know nothing about.

Sure, China owns 80% of the market, and have had some major fuck-ups making toys, painting some toys with lead paint is all I can recall, yet you cannot simply say “They don’t even get sued”, you can’t say that at all. For one, How the fuck can you sue a whole country? And two, It’s YOUR own ignorant country that failed to check the safety of the toys, your government is to blame, since they have the responsibility to check the safety of ALL imported objects.

But yes, we can all happily blame China for the rising cost in copper and food.

There to lazy to check them, so they wait till the US files a callback on the toy to save them time. You’re retarded. The US’s job is to check for imports. You can’t blame it entirely on China, especially when they’re not ignorant.

And like I said, Chinese jobs aren’t as well-paying as you may think, and opportunity is much more limited there. A job is a job, whether or not they affect 10 year olds’ games or not.
